problem.markdown:
>> What is a saddle point? <<

( ) It is a local minimum with non-zero gradients.  {{A saddle point is not a minimum. A saddle point also has gradients of zero, which is why it is difficult to escape saddle points.}}
( ) It is a local maximum with gradients of zero. {{A saddle point is not a maximum.}}
( ) It is neither a local minimum, not a local maximum, but it has non-zero gradients. {{A saddle point has gradients of zero, which is why it is difficult to escape saddle points.}}
(x) It is neither a local minimum, nor a local maximum, but it has gradients of zero. {{Saddle points are not extrema, but they have zero gradients, making them problematic during optimization.}}

||Please refer to the classification of critical points in the video 3.3.1a- Introduction - Part I. ||
